modules.description: Reads and inspects a manifest embedded in an ELF executable stored in memory, extracting device requirements and configuration details. Processes ELF file structures and manifest data encoded in the binary's metadata. Enables direct inspection of unikernel device expectations without disk I/O, useful for runtime validation and analysis.

Parses and pretty-prints Solo5 manifest and ABI data from a file descriptor, using custom pretty-printers for structured output. Works with types representing manifest entries, the manifest itself, and ABI targets and versions. Used to extract and display metadata from Solo5-compatible binaries during runtime validation.
